         <abstract>
            <p>The collection of the Miracles of Mary is one of the most popular works of Gǝʿǝz literature.
               It circulates as collections of varying constitution, of which the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5673AkkonuColl"/> is the most standardised one.
                In the unpublished list compiled by William
               Macomber, <bibl><ptr target="bm:MacomberMiracles"/></bibl>, 
               642 individual miracles are listed.</p>
            <p>This record refers to any collection of the Miracles of Mary declared as such and
               containing in addition to the miracles also introductory texts such as the <ref
                  type="work" corresp="LIT1968Mashaf"/>. For groups of miracles of Mary without introductory texts,
               see <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3585Taamme"/>, for the so-called <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾAkko-nu bǝʾsi</foreign> collection of 33 miracles, see
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5673AkkonuColl"/>.</p>
         </abstract>
